Throws if `from` is not the current owner. Throws if `to` is the zero address. Throws if `tokenId` is not a valid NFT. When transfer is complete, this function checks if `to` is a smart contract (code size > 0). If so, it calls `onERC721Received` on `to` and throws if the return value is not `bytes4(keccak256("onERC721Received(address,address,uint256,bytes)"))`.
